<subSubSection id="C3356FE2013B5361FCADFEBCC60DFE26" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="18" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B903C69013B5361FCADFEBCC60DFE26" blockId="18.[820,1432,198,613]" lastBlockId="19.[156,768,198,1133]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013B5360FCADFEBCC4B4FEB8" bold="true" box="[846,958,263,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="549482CB013B5360FC26FEBCC329FEB8" box="[965,1059,263,287]" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Holotype</typeStatus>
7.7 mm long for 61 chaetigers, body dark grey. Median antenna subulate, slightly longer than prostomium; lateral antennae similar, but 2/3 as long; palps similar to lateral antennae (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FBBEFED2C3B7FE26" box="[1117,1213,361,385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
). Proboscis with ten conical marginal papillae (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FBB3FE32C3BAFE06" box="[1104,1200,393,417]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
). Parapodia biramous with reduced notopodia (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FBDAFE11C3B9FE65" box="[1081,1203,426,450]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15C, D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal cirri in chaetigers 1 and 2 shorter than subsequent ones (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FAE6FE71C26AFE45" box="[1285,1376,458,482]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15A</figureCitation>
); notopodial lobes supported by a single acicula (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FAE4FE50C268FDA4" box="[1287,1378,491,515]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15G</figureCitation>
) and bearing gently sigmoid pectinate chaetae without spur (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FA93FDB7C451FDE3" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15F</figureCitation>
) and 15–20 acicular simple chaetae (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013B5360FB03FD97C231FDE3" box="[1248,1339,556,580]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
). Neuropodial lobes bearing compound chaetae with blades having coarse basal serration and rounded tips (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FDA1FF7DC5AAFF79" box="[578,672,198,222]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15H</figureCitation>
), or with blades having fine serration and unidentate (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FD85FF5CC5BCFF58" box="[614,694,231,255]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15J</figureCitation>
) or bidentate (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FF15FEBCC65BFEB8" box="[246,337,263,287]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15K</figureCitation>
) tips, and simple chaetae with (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FD43FEBCC5FDFEB8" box="[672,759,263,287]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15L</figureCitation>
) or without (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FEFFFE93C67AFEE7" box="[284,368,296,320]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15I</figureCitation>
) clearly bifid tips. Posterior end with fan-shaped anal membrane fringed with 37 small papillae (
<figureCitation id="131420EC013A5361FF40FED2C7F1FE26" box="[163,251,361,385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[158,189,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,664,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-199@18.[187,1400,662,1906]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 15. Microphthalmus itoi sp. nov., holotype (NSMT Pol H-760). A, dorsal view of the anterior body. B, dorsal view of the posterior end. C, posterior view of right parapodium 9. D, anterior view of right parapodium 53. E, notopodial simple chaeta. F, notopodial pectinate chaeta. G, notopodial acicula from chaetiger 9. H, neuropodial superiormost serrated chaeta. I, neuropodial superior simple chaeta. J, long type of neuropodial compound chaeta. K, short type of neuropodial compound chaeta. L, neuropodial inferior simple chaeta. Scale bar: 0.2mm for A; 0.1mm for B–D; 0.02mm for E–L." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5738431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5738431/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
