<subSubSection id="C3356FE2013A5361FF56FE31C66AFE44" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B903C69013A5361FF56FE31C66AFE44" blockId="19.[156,768,198,1133]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FF56FE31C627FE05" bold="true" box="[181,301,394,418]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of the late Dr. Tatsunori Itô, who collected the 
<typeStatus id="549482CB013A5361FEB8FE11C6BEFE65" box="[347,436,426,450]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">holotype</typeStatus>
during his survey of interstitial fauna in 
<collectingRegion id="49EBF28B013A5361FF16FE70C656FE44" box="[245,348,459,483]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356FE2013A5361FF56FE50C6ECFBCA" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B903C69013A5361FF56FE50C6ECFBCA" blockId="19.[156,768,198,1133]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FF56FE50C613FDA4" bold="true" box="[181,281,491,515]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Remarks.</emphasis>
The detailed description of the 
<typeStatus id="549482CB013A5361FD8EFE57C593FDA3" box="[621,665,492,516]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
materials was presented in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FEBEFDB7C6F2FD83" author="Uchida, H." box="[349,504,524,548]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="27 - 92" refId="ref21488" refString="Uchida, H. 2004. Hesionidae (Annelida, Polichaeta [sic]) from Japan. I. Kuroshio Biosphere 1: 27 - 92." type="journal article" year="2004">Uchida (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FDE4FDB7C5D2FD84" authority="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato, 2019" authorityName="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato" authorityYear="2019" box="[519,728,524,548]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="itoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FDE4FDB7C5D2FD84" box="[519,728,524,548]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Microphthalmus itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2685D00013A5361FD00FDB7C7CDFDE3" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by having fringed anal membrane, neuropodial simple and compound chaetae combined, pectinate notochaeta, and more than ten simple chaetae in each notopodial lobe. The new species shares these characters with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FD00FD34C684FD61" authority="Bobretzky, 1870" authorityName="Bobretzky" authorityYear="1870" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FD00FD34C7D5FD61" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. fragilis</emphasis>
Bobretzky, 1870
</taxonomicName>
, from Europe, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FDBFFD14C630FD40" authority="Alikunhi, 1943" authorityName="Alikunhi" authorityYear="1943" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="urofimbriata">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FDBFFD14C5F4FD61" box="[604,766,686,710]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. urofimbriata</emphasis>
Alikunhi, 1943
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="F3387CF9013A5361FE60FD74C6B1FD40" box="[387,443,719,743]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">India</collectingCountry>
. However, pectinate notochaetae are gently sigmoid in the new species and in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FD47FD4BC7B8FC8F" authorityName="Bobretzky" authorityYear="1870" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FD47FD4BC7B8FC8F" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, instead of being bow-shaped as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FDC6FCAAC616FCEE" authority="(Alikunhi 1948)" baseAuthorityName="Alikunhi" baseAuthorityYear="1948" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="urofimbriata">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FDC6FCAAC5CCFC8F" box="[549,710,784,808]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. urofimbriata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FD36FCABC61CFCEE" author="Alikunhi, K. H." pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="17 - 25" refId="ref19678" refString="Alikunhi, K. H. 1948. On a new hermaphrodite species of Microphthalmus (Polychaeta-Hesionidae) from the sandy beach, Madras. Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Bengal, Science 14: 17 - 25." type="journal article" year="1948">Alikunhi 1948</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FE5AFC8AC52BFCEF" authorityName="Bobretzky" authorityYear="1870" box="[441,545,816,840]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FE5AFC8AC52BFCEF" box="[441,545,816,840]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species in having a more complex fringe in anal membrane (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FF40FCC9C63FFC2E" author="LaGreca, M." box="[163,309,881,906]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref20350" refString="LaGreca, M. 1950. Sulla presenza nel Mediterraneo di Lycastoides pontica (Bobr.), Microphthalmus fragilis Bobr. e M. similis Bobr. (Annelida, Polychaeta). Annuario dell'Istituto e Museo di Zoologia dell'Universita di Napoli 2: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1950">LaGreca 1950</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FEA3FCC9C50EFC2D" author="Parapar, J. &amp; Besteiro, C. &amp; Moreira, J." box="[320,516,881,906]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="210 - 267" refId="ref21036" refString="Parapar, J., Besteiro, C., and Moreira, J. 2004. Familia Hesionidae Grube, 1850. Pp. 210 - 267. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds) Annelida, Polychaeta I. Fauna Iberica, Vol. 25. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales / CSIC, Madrid." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Parapar 
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FE74FCC9C6C0FC2E" box="[407,458,881,905]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
) and bow-shaped pectinate chaetae without a conspicuous spur. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FDBFFC29C6C1FC6C" authority="Westheide, 1974" authorityName="Westheide" authorityYear="1974" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="indefatigatus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FDBFFC29C616FC6D" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Microphthalmus indefatigatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FEC7FC09C6C1FC6C" author="Westheide, W." box="[292,459,946,971]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref21784" refString="Westheide, W. 1974. Interstitielle Fauna von Galapagos, XI. Pisionidae, Hesionidae, Pilargidae, Syllidae (Polychaeta). Mikrofauna des Meeresbodens 44: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1974">Westheide, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the only previously known species with neuropodial compound chaetae having both 
<typeStatus id="549482CB013A5361FF7FFC4FC7DBFBAB" box="[156,209,1012,1036]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">types</typeStatus>
of tips, entire and bifid (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4198013A5361FE29FC4FC565FBAB" author="Westheide, W." box="[458,623,1012,1036]" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref21784" refString="Westheide, W. 1974. Interstitielle Fauna von Galapagos, XI. Pisionidae, Hesionidae, Pilargidae, Syllidae (Polychaeta). Mikrofauna des Meeresbodens 44: 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1974">Westheide 1974</bibRefCitation>
), as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FD78FC4FC5D4FBAC" authority="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato, 2019" authorityName="Hiro &amp; Uchida &amp; Lopéz &amp; Sato" authorityYear="2019" box="[667,734,1012,1035]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="itoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FD78FC4FC5D4FBAC" box="[667,734,1012,1035]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2685D00013A5361FD00FC4FC7CDFB8B" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F47EA013A5361FDBFFBAEC5F5FB8B" authorityName="Westheide" authorityYear="1974" box="[604,767,1044,1068]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Microphthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="indefatigatus">
<emphasis id="B95BE07B013A5361FDBFFBAEC5F5FB8B" box="[604,767,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">M. indefatigatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having short notocirri, long pectinate notochaetae, and more notopodial simple chaetae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
